[2026-03-18T12:01:20.184Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014ZXomvdN1yP1UFCJH87NGL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 5 ideas saved successfully. Here's the summary:\n\n## Observability Scout - Event Bus & Subscriptions\n\n**5 ideas created** in scan `1eaf3f6b-6f66-4dbc-a9a0-81a85c760238`:\n\n| # | Title | Category | Effort | Impact | Risk |\n|---|-------|----------|--------|--------|------|\n| 1 | Add tick-level timing and outcome metrics to event processor | code_quality | 2 | 8 | 1 |\n| 2 | Expose event processor health in /health endpoint | functionality | 3 | 8 | 2 |\n| 3 | Separate concurrency-limited skips from actual failures | code_quality | 2 | 7 | 1 |\n| 4 | Log malformed event payload parse failures | code_quality | 1 | 6 | 1 |\n| 5 | Add event-to-execution correlation tracing | functionality | 4 | 9 | 3 |\n\n### Key observations from the codebase:\n\n- **The event processor loop (`eventBusTick`) is completely opaque** — it runs every 2s but emits no per-cycle telemetry. You can't tell \"no pending events\" from \"processor crashed.\"\n- **Silent failure at line 79** — malformed JSON payloads are silently downgraded to `{ raw: payload }` with zero logging, hiding upstream integration bugs.\n- **Concurrency throttling counted as failure** — `failed++` at line 70 conflates normal backpressure with genuine errors, making failure rates misleading.\n- **No event→execution traceability** — the `executionId` is generated at dispatch but the originating `eventId` isn't threaded through, breaking the debug chain.\n- **`/health` endpoint is blind to the event processor** — only reports workers and OAuth, missing the event bus entirely."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3338,"cache_read_input_tokens":54098,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3338},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier